# Firebase Firestore and Storage Rules

Per core invariants. Firestore and Storage security rules are part of the project and must stay in sync with how the app uses Firebase.

## Rules Location

- **Firestore rules:** `firebase/firestore.rules` — source of truth for Firestore access control.
- **Storage rules:** `firebase/storage.rules` — source of truth for Storage access control.
- **Config:** Root `firebase.json` references these files for deployment (`firebase deploy --only firestore`, `firebase deploy --only storage`).

Do not put rules in project root. All rule content lives under `firebase/`.

## When to Update Rules

Whenever you **add or change** Firestore or Storage usage in the app, update the corresponding rules and docs:

- **New Firestore collection or path** (e.g. a new `users/{uid}/something` subcollection) → add or adjust a `match` in `firebase/firestore.rules` so access is allowed only for the intended callers (e.g. `request.auth.uid == userId`). Do not leave new paths covered only by a broad deny; add an explicit allow for the new path and keep an explicit deny for everything else.
- **New Storage path or pattern** (e.g. a new folder under the bucket) → add or adjust a `match` in `firebase/storage.rules` with the correct ownership condition.
- **Change in who may read/write** (e.g. admin access, different user scope) → update the condition in the relevant `match` in `firebase/firestore.rules` or `firebase/storage.rules`.

After changing rules, **update documentation** per documentation-integrity: `docs/18-FIREBASE-FIRESTORE-STORAGE.md` (and any other doc that describes Firebase paths or security) must reflect the current structure and deployment steps.

## Current App Usage

- **Firestore:** `users/{userId}/orders/{orderId}` (template request orders; owner read/write with counter rules and Whop gating on submit/non-draft updates), `users/{userId}/access/{docId}` (Whop entitlement — owner read; **client write denied**), `users/{userId}/requestLimits/{limitId}` (daily counter), `users/{userId}/reports/{reportId}` (issue reports — **client denied**; writes only via Admin SDK from `POST /api/reports/issue`). Catch-all deny for everything else.
- **Storage:** Only `orders/{userId}/{orderId}/{fileName}` is used (order attachments). Owner-only read/write.

Any new collection or path must be added to the rules explicitly; the catch-all deny in Firestore must remain so that only intended paths are allowed.

## Deployment

Rules are deployed via Firebase CLI from project root: `firebase deploy --only firestore`, `firebase deploy --only storage`, or both. See `docs/18-FIREBASE-FIRESTORE-STORAGE.md` for deployment and Console fallback.

Reference `docs/18-FIREBASE-FIRESTORE-STORAGE.md` for the full data model and security layout.
